{{Infobox religious building | name = Maria Kannon Zen Center | native_name = | image = Ruben Habito.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = [[Ruben Habito]], guiding teacher | map_type = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | location = White Rock UMC 1450 Old Gate Lane Room 202 Dallas, TX 75218 | coordinates = | religious_affiliation = [[Sanbo Kyodan]] | deity = | country = [[United States]] | functional_status = | website = [http://www.mkzc.org/ http://www.mkzc.org/] | founded_by = | year_completed = 1991 }} '''Maria Kannon Zen Center''' (MKZC) is a [[non-profit]] practice center in the [[Sanbo Kyodan]] tradition of [[Zen Buddhism]], located in [[Dallas, Texas]] and founded in 1991 by the guiding teacher [[Ruben Habito]] (a [[Dharma heir]] of [[Yamada Koun]]).<ref name="post">Post; xiii</ref> MKZC derives its name by combining the names of the [[Virgin Mary]] of [[Christianity]] and [[Kannon]] [[bodhisattva]] of [[Buddhism]]. It is actually the name of a figurine revered in [[Japan]] during Christian persecution there.<ref>Habito</ref> Many of the MKZC members are individuals who consider themselves Christian, with Habito himself being a practicing [[Catholic]] and former [[Jesuit]] priest.<ref>Ford; 184</ref> MKZC is listed with the [[American Zen Teachers Association]].[https://web.archive.org/web/20080907090615/http://americanzenteachers.org/list.html]
